{{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |name = Komushi Shrine | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = [[File:与謝野町温江 子虫神社.jpg|300px]] |location = [[:en:Kyoto Prefecture|Kyoto Prefecture]], [[Yosa District]], [[Yosano Town]], Atsue, Omoriya 103 |coordinates = {{ill|Wikicoordinates|en|ウィキ座標2段度分秒|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wikicoordinates|qq=}}|35|30|02.7|N|135|06|31.8|E|scale:25000 |deity = {{ill|Sukunabikona no Mikoto|ja|少彦名命|1=Sukunabikona|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スクナビコナ}} |Rank = {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 延喜式神名帳}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin Taisha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 名神大社}}), Former Village Shrine |founded = Unknown |main_hall = [[:en:Shinmei-zukuri|Shinmei-zukuri]] |alias = |festival = Last Sunday in April |ceremonies = Kayadani Festival (last Saturday and Sunday in April) }}
'''Komushi Shrine''' ({{ill|Komushi Shrine|ja|小虫神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Komushi Shrine|qq=}}) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Atsue]], [[Yosano Town]], [[Yosa District]], [[:en:Kyoto Prefecture|Kyoto Prefecture]]. It is a designated {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 延喜式神名帳}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin Taisha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 名神大社}}) and Ranked as a [[Village Shrine]] under the [[Modern typeing System]]. The shrine is situated on an eastern plateau of the Kayadani area along the midstream of the {{ill|Nodagawa River (Kyoto)|ja|野田川|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nodagawa River (Kyoto)|qq=}}, at the western base of the Ōeyama mountain range. Kayadani is known for its concentration of ancient Kofuns and archaeological sites, such as the nationally designated [[Hiruko-yama Kofun]] and the [[Sakuyama Kofun (Yosano Town)|Sakuyama Kofun]], making it a key area in the ancient [[Tango Province]].
== Deities == * {{ill|Sukunabikona no Mikoto|ja|少彦名命|1=Sukunabikona|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スクナビコナ}} (The shrine records from 1883 note an alternate tradition enshrining "Wakayama-kui no Mikoto." <ref>Included in Volume 1 of the "Kayachō History: Materials Edition."</ref>) * {{ill|Kagutsuchi no Mikoto|ja|火産霊命|1=Kagu-tsuchi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagutsuchi no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagu-tsuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to カグツチ}} (from Hirogaki Shrine, merged in 1877) * {{ill|Ōyamatsumi no Mikoto|ja|大山祇命|1=Ōyamatsumi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to オオヤマツミ}} (from Kijimi Shrine, merged simultaneously with Hirogaki Shrine)
The primary deity, {{ill|Sukunabikona no Mikoto|ja|少彦名命|1=Sukunabikona|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to スクナビコナ}} (or Wakayama-kui no Mikoto), is regarded as the god responsible for the construction of Yosa District and the guardian deity of hot springs.<ref>Kayachō History. Regarding the current location of "Atsue," the [[Meiji period]] scholar {{ill|Yoshida Tōgo|ja|吉田東伍|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Tōgo|qq=}} suggested the name originated from the ancient presence of hot springs, although no springs remain as of the Meiji era.</ref>
